The paper deals with the problem of target tracking with multiple robots, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also introduces planning algorithms for multi-target tracking, which involves artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and provides provable bounds, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses simulations to demonstrate the efficacy of the algorithm, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV).
